  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Saldanha Real Estate Private Limited  versus Bishop John Rodrigues and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_8_1379_1412','2025INSC1016'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SALDANHA REAL ESTATE PRIVATE LIMITED <span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>BISHOP JOHN RODRIGUES AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 1379</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1016</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006442025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SURYA KANT<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the validity of the acquisition of land under Maharashtra Slum Areas (Improvement, Clearance and Redevelopment) Act, 1971; whether the High Court rightly rejected the Society&rsquo;s preliminary objection; whether the 2018 Amendment impacts in Tarabai&rsquo;s case; and whether the High Court rightly set aside the public notice and the order approving the acquisition proposal. Headnotes&dagger; Maharashtra Slum Areas (Improvement, Clearance and Redevelopment) (Amendment) Act, 2017 &ndash; ss.3B, 3C(1) &ndash; Maharashtra Slum Areas<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 22-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 11008/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_8_1379_1412','2025INSC1016','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'>